Questions:
What will happen if you choose to withdraw your participation from the research study?
A) You will be required to pay a penalty fee for early withdrawal;
B) You will no longer be eligible for any medical care at Henry Ford Hospital;
C) You may continue to use and release information that has already been collected, but cannot collect new information;
D) Your participation in the study will end, and no further personal health information will be collected or used for the study.

Correct answer: D

If you experience an injury related to the research study, whom should you contact for assistance?

A) The FDA or other regulatory agencies;
B) Dr. Ian Lee, the Principal Investigator, or his staff;
C) Your insurance company;
D) The Henry Ford Health IRB Administration Office.

Correct answer: B) Dr. Ian Lee, the Principal Investigator, or his staff.
